name: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez
tweet: Yes. Full transparency: My issues w/ non-emergency UBI have to do w/ domino effects that have not been sufficiently addressed: triggering mass disqualification thresholds on Medicaid, SNAP, & many other programs, inflationary concerns, etc.  I‚Äôm open to it but we need to bake it.

name: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez
tweet: People have harped on me about ‚ÄúTrojan horse‚Äù comments I‚Äôve made before abt UBI policies,but seriously: not every UBI policy is created equal.  Some are structured in predatory ways to gut the safety net & reward banks, others are better w/people‚Äôs well-being in mind. Be careful.

name: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez
tweet: Cash is important but if you do it w/o payment suspensions then it‚Äôs still everyday people footing the bill.  Corporations, lenders, and banks need to do their fair share.  UBI shouldn‚Äôt be used as an excuse for not pausing mortgage & student loan payments, halting interest, etc.

name: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez
tweet: These proposals should be handled with care and consideration, particularly with respect to macroeconomic effects.  But they should be considered nevertheless.  Other countries are getting by w/ payment suspensions, which also creates that cash buffer.

name: Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez
tweet: One way or another we are going to have to address liquidity shock that Americans are facing.  Whether it‚Äôs UBI, mortgage/rent/loan suspensions, or other means, if we do not act quickly many people will go hungry, be driven out of their homes, or confront other extreme harms.
